casebody.data:
GRABINA v. UNITED STATES. No. 851,

Misc.

Decided April 16, 1962. Petitioner pro se. Solicitor General Cox, Assistant Attorney General Miller, Beatrice Rosenberg and Theodore George Gilin-sky for the United States. Per Curiam.

In light of the concession by the Solicitor General and upon an examination of the entire record, the motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for writ of certiorari are granted. The judgment is vacated and the case is remanded to the District Court for resentencing.

Mr. Justice Frankfurter and Mr. Justice White took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
